 <sect1 id="gkb-intro">
  <title>The GNOME keyboard switcher applet</title>

  <para>
    The <application>GNOME gkb applet</application> displays a small
    flag in your <interface>panel</interface> and does nothing useful 
    whatsoever beyond that. After all, if you click on this flag, you can
    change your keyboard map. It is part of the gnome-core package. This 
    description of it refers to the gkb as displayed in gnome-applets-1.2.
  </para>
  <para>
    It is occasionally found in the <interface>panel</interface> anyway, 
    but if you don't see it, you can start it by clicking <mousebutton>button
    3</mousebutton> on an empty part of the <interface>panel</interface>
    and following the sequence
   <menuchoice>
   <guimenu>Applets</guimenu>
    <guisubmenu>Tools</guisubmenu>
    <guimenuitem>gkb</guimenuitem>
   </menuchoice>
  </para>
  <para>
    The gkb applet was written by Szabolcs Ban (<email>shooby@gnome.hu</email>). 
    Please report bugs in it to the
    <ulink type="http" url="http://bugs.gnome.org">GNOME bug tracking 
    system</ulink>. You can do this by following the guidelines on that site 
    or by using <command>bug-buddy</command> from the command-line. 
    For the package, put gnome-core.
  </para>

  <sect2 id="gkb-usage">
   <title>Usage</title>

   <para>
    First, you need to start the properties window...
   </para>

   <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
       If you have the <application>fortune</application> package installed,
       pressing <mousebutton>mouse button 1</mousebutton> switches the
       keymap to the next.
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Pressing <mousebutton>mouse button 2</mousebutton> and holding it
      down allows you to drag your gkb about.

     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
       Pressing <mousebutton>mouse button 3</mousebutton> brings up a
       menu which includes a <guisubmenu>preferences menu</guisubmenu> and
       an <guimenuitem>About</guimenuitem> box. 

       <figure id="GKB-MENU-fig1">
