  </sect2>

  <sect2 id="gkb-prefs">
   <title>Properties</title>
   <para>
     The <guilabel>properties dialog box</guilabel> (called
     GKB Properties) is simple.
     Every tab is a keymap. At every keymap set you can set the name of the
     set, the full command, (there is a gkb_xmmap script for xmodmap) the
     iconpath.
   </para>
   <para>
   You can do new keymap and delete the actual.
   </para>
   <para>
   The commad sould be like this: "gkb_xmmap us" or "setxkbmap fr" or
   "/usr/local/bin/Xmodmap ru".
   </para> 
 <figure id="GKB-Prefs-fig1">
  <title>GKB Properties dialog box</title>
  <screenshot>
   <screeninfo>GKB Properties dialog box</screeninfo>
   <graphic format="png" fileref="preferences" srccredit="Szabolcs BAN">
   </graphic>
  </screenshot>
 </figure>

   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
     <term>Your GNOME gkb's keymap name</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
        You can change your gkb's keymap name here. The default name is us.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
     <term>The icon filename</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
        You can select a different set of pictures here. By default, 
        the list of pictures is in <filename>$PREFIX/pixmaps/gkb/</filename>,
        which you can browse and choose from. 

